    • Field Detail

      • STRING_VAL_SERIALIZATION_SUFFIX

        public static java.lang.String STRING_VAL_SERIALIZATION_SUFFIX
        We use this string value constant to add as a suffix to, a string value that is getting serialized by Xalan-J serializer, when XSL serialization is getting done during evaluation of xsl:sequence instruction. This helps us construct later during XSL transformation process, a sequence of xdm atomic values. We're assuming that, this string value is significantly random, and is unlikely to exist within an input document that is getting transformed by Xalan-J.
